                            <comment id="13442122" author="iorixxx" created="Sun, 26 Aug 2012 16:49:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;missing AdminHandlers for tika core and PingRequestHandler for all cores.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13442151" author="lancenorskog" created="Sun, 26 Aug 2012 19:36:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Cool! This is an illustration of why &quot;one big example&quot; is better: people test it!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The convention in solr/ is to add solr.xml and collection1:&lt;br/&gt;
solr/solr.xml&lt;br/&gt;
solr/collection1&lt;br/&gt;
solr/collection1/conf&lt;br/&gt;
... &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please change example-DIH/solr to match this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13457231" author="hossman" created="Mon, 17 Sep 2012 19:07:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for your patch Ahmet, I also added the admin-extra files so the UI wouldn&apos;t complain...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 1386773.&lt;br/&gt;
Committed revision 1386774. - 4x&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;The convention in solr/ is to add solr.xml and collection1: ...&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I did not make that change.  the collection1 default/convention makes sense for the generic example where there is a single collection that can be used for a variety of purposes &amp;#8211; in the case of example-DIH ther are 5 collections each demonstrating a very specific thing and each has a very specific name.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13610818" author="commit-tag-bot" created="Fri, 22 Mar 2013 16:37:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;branch_4x commit&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Chris M. Hostetter&lt;br/&gt;
